IoT devices are connected to the internet, and this gives us an advantage for product updates. 
When new functionality or bug fixes are developed, we can use the internet to push updates to our IoT devices. 

This process is easy when using an SBC. 
you just push the udate as you would for any software. 

If your product uses a microcontroller or FPGA, then thing get a bit more complicated. 
Your device will need to download a firmware image, and then transfer that into non-volatile memory as required. 

FIRST, it is essential for security that any firmware update is authenticated. 
